{
  "texts": [
    "Next, Algorithm bias refers to the bias that may be introduced into machine learning models by the algorithms used to train them.",
    "This bias can result from the selection of a particular algorithm or from how we implement the algorithm.",
    "Finally, User-generated data bias refers to the bias when we train the model with user-generated data that may reflect the biases and preferences of the users who generated it rather than being representative of the population as a whole.",
    "These review articles emphasize discussing the adopted fairness-ensuring methodologies and often classify these methodologies.",
    "Generally, they classify these methodologies into pre-processing, in-processing, and post-processing [30,31]."
  ]
}